        "United States",
        [
          "/wiki/United_States"
        ]
      ],
      [
        "Black Rock Canal flows within and parallel to the east shore of the Niagara river near Buffalo , New York , and was built to extend the navigation period in the Niagara River through a greater part of the winter . The canal begins at Buffalo Harbor , on the north-east shore of Lake Erie , then flows north , ending at the Black Rock Lock near the north tip of Unity Island . The canal is buffered from the Niagara River by Bird Island Pier at its south end , and Unity Island at its north end",
        [
          "/wiki/Buffalo,_New_York",
          "/wiki/Black_Rock_Lock",
          "/wiki/Unity_Island"
        ]
      ]
    ],
